Boil a full #kettle{}.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat.

Add the @linguine{180%grams} and @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve some of the pasta water, then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the linguine back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it from sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} and shallot and cook, stirring frequently, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Pour in the @reserved pasta water{75%milliliter} and @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, stir together, then bring to the boil. Simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Drain the @king prawns{150%grams}.

Stir the prawns, diced chicken and @peas{120%grams} into the sauce and cook for another ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so the prawns are opaque in the middle.

Once the chicken and prawns are cooked, stir the @creme fraiche{75%grams} and lemon zest into the sauce. Bring back to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Season with @pepper{}, then stir through the cooked pasta.

Add a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lemon juice if needed.

When ready, share the prawn linguine between your bowls.

Serve with any remaining lemon cut into wedges for squeezing over.

> This delicious Prawn and Chicken Lemon Linguine has been expertly designed as a lighter option to help with a balanced lifestyle.